## 1. Add Dependencies

Add these to your `build.gradle` (Module):

```gradle
// Retrofit & OkHttp
implementation 'com.squareup.retrofit2:retrofit:2.9.0'
implementation 'com.squareup.retrofit2:converter-gson:2.9.0'
implementation 'com.squareup.okhttp3:logging-interceptor:4.9.3'

// Hilt
implementation 'com.google.dagger:hilt-android:2.44'
kapt 'com.google.dagger:hilt-android-compiler:2.44'
```

## 2. Create Retrofit API Interface

Suppose you have a Supabase edge function at 
`https://your-project-id.supabase.co/functions/v1/my-edge-func`:

```kotlin
interface SupabaseEdgeApi {
 @POST("my-edge-func")
 suspend fun callMyEdgeFunc(@Body params: MyEdgeFuncRequest): Response<MyEdgeFuncResponse>
}
```

## 3. Hilt Module for Providing Retrofit

Create a module for Hilt to provide Retrofit and your API:

```kotlin
@Module
@InstallIn(SingletonComponent::class)
object NetworkModule {

 @Provides
 fun provideBaseUrl(): String = "https://your-project-id.supabase.co/functions/v1/"

 @Singleton
 @Provides
 fun provideOkHttpClient(): OkHttpClient =
 OkHttpClient.Builder()
 .addInterceptor(HttpLoggingInterceptor().apply {
 level = HttpLoggingInterceptor.Level.BODY
 })
 .build()

 @Singleton
 @Provides
 fun provideRetrofit(
 baseUrl: String,
 client: OkHttpClient
 ): Retrofit = Retrofit.Builder()
 .baseUrl(baseUrl)
 .addConverterFactory(GsonConverterFactory.create())
 .client(client)
 .build()

 @Singleton
 @Provides
 fun provideSupabaseEdgeApi(retrofit: Retrofit): SupabaseEdgeApi =
 retrofit.create(SupabaseEdgeApi::class.java)
}
```

## 4. Inject the API in Your Repository or ViewModel

```kotlin
@HiltViewModel
class MyViewModel @Inject constructor(
 private val api: SupabaseEdgeApi
) : ViewModel() {

 fun callEdgeFunction() {
 viewModelScope.launch {
 val response = api.callMyEdgeFunc(/* Your params */)
 // Handle response
 }
 }
}
```

## 5. Application Setup

Don’t forget to annotate your `Application` class for Hilt:

```kotlin
@HiltAndroidApp
class MyApp : Application()
```

